description:
What can we learn from a typological study of the devastating plagues of Egypt?  What does it teach about God’s final deliverance of His people? Just before God delivered His people from Egypt, ten plagues fell upon the people of the land. The same chronology is followed in the seven last plagues of Revelation. What can we learn from the types (the 10 plagues in Egypt) and the antitypes (the seven last plagues in Revelation)? Francois du Plessis looks at the typology of the Egyptian plagues and reveals the meaning of the symbols. What lessons are there for us? 

Discover anew God’s love and longsuffering for those who reject Him and those who accept Him.
